# Stakeholder map — [APP_NAME]

Who approves what. Who is impacted by what. Where to escalate when blocked.

This file is read by `rsct_get_knowledge(category="stakeholder-map")` during
spec phase when the task touches areas with named approval gates. The phase
brief will surface the relevant stakeholder so the dev knows up-front "this
needs Marcos before it can ship" — instead of discovering it at merge time.

A senior engineer knows who to loop in before starting work; a junior
discovers it the hard way. This file closes that gap.

---

## When to capture an entry here

Capture a stakeholder when **any** of the following is true:

- A person/role has **explicit approval authority** over a class of changes
("all auth changes pass through Carla", "fiscal/tax changes require Marcos
sign-off").
- An approval was missed and caused rework or rollback. Capture the lesson.
- A new hire, contractor, vendor PM, or board member acquires a formal scope.
- A regulator, auditor, or compliance officer must be looped in for specific
operations (LGPD DPO for data processing changes, fiscal auditor for invoicing).
- A customer is a named stakeholder (large account with single-tenant SLAs,
strategic pilot, or veto right by contract).

## When NOT to capture here

- Team members without approval scope → `team-capabilities.md` (their skills
and current load).
- People mentioned in passing without authority → don't capture; mention
in the relevant ADR or incident if needed.
- Personal info (private phone numbers, home addresses) → never. Channels
only.
- Stakeholders of other projects → keep this file scoped to [APP_NAME].
Cross-project stakeholders live in `universe/applications/<app>/README.md`
or `universe/docs/governance/document-control.md`.

---

## Entry schema

Each entry follows this exact structure:

```
### SH-NNN — <Name or Role>
- **Role:** <title; if internal, include team; if external, include org>
- **Approves:** <bullet list of change classes they sign off on. Be specific —
  not "anything backend" but "schema migrations affecting financial tables",
  not "frontend" but "public-facing brand and copy changes">
- **Cares about:** <modules, flows, metrics they actively track — used by
  rsct_persona_review to surface their concerns even when approval isn't needed>
- **Reach via:** <primary channel, expected response time>
- **Escalation when unavailable:** <fallback person or process>
- **Do NOT bring them:** <changes outside their scope that they'd find noise.
  Optional but powerful — protects everyone's time>
- **Captured:** <YYYY-MM-DD> by <dev|claude>
```

Numbering: SH-001, SH-002, ... sequential, append-only. When someone leaves
a role, mark `Status: archived YYYY-MM-DD` rather than deleting — historical
context matters when reading old PRs.

---

## Example entries (✅ good — keep this style)

### SH-002 — Marcos Andrade
- **Role:** CFO (Acme Corp) — financial operations and tax compliance owner
- **Approves:**
  - Any change to invoicing, billing, fiscal-document generation (NFe, NFSe)
  - Any change to tax calculation rules (PIS/COFINS/ISS/ICMS rates and rules)
  - Migration of any financial table schema (anything in `finance.*` namespace)
  - New payment provider integration or change in capture/refund flow
- **Cares about:** monthly close timeline (5th business day), audit-trail completeness, deferred-revenue accuracy.
- **Reach via:** Slack #finance-eng channel; response within ~4 business hours; for urgent: WhatsApp via Sara (CFO's EA).
- **Escalation when unavailable:** João (Accounting Lead) for pre-approval on routine; defer non-urgent to Marcos return.
- **Do NOT bring them:** UI copy changes, non-fiscal report tweaks, dev-environment configuration, anything in modules outside `finance.*` or `tax.*`.
- **Captured:** 2025-10-15 by alice

### SH-005 — Customer: Largo Brasil S.A. (single-tenant SLA)
- **Role:** Strategic enterprise account; signed single-tenant DB requirement (see [[anti-decisions]] AD-003 context)
- **Approves:**
  - Any change to API endpoints they consume (contract changes require 30-day notice per contract Cláusula 7.2)
  - Maintenance windows on their tenant (must be > 7 days advance, never on month-end)
- **Cares about:** API uptime, audit log delivery to their SIEM, response time on `/reports/financial`.
- **Reach via:** customer-success channel (Bia owns); Largo's technical contact is Engenheiro Hugo Tavares (hugo@largo.com.br).
- **Escalation when unavailable:** customer-success leadership; never reach customer directly without Bia's handoff.
- **Do NOT bring them:** product roadmap discussion (sales handles), pricing (sales handles), other customers' issues.
- **Captured:** 2025-10-15 by alice

